IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: Perpetuate the memory of our Pilgrim Fathers, Maintain and defend principles of civil & religious liberty as set forth in the Mayflower compact. To cherish & maintain the ideas and institutions of American freedom & to oppose any theories or actions that threaten their continuity.
IRS990.MissionDesc: To perpetuate the memory of our pilgrim fathers. To maintain and defend the principles of civil & religious liberty as set forth in The Compact of the Mayflower, "For the glory of God, and the advancements of the Christian faith and honor our country." To cherish and maintain the ideals and institutions of American freedom, and oppose any theories or actions that threaten their continuity. To transmit the spirit, the purity of purpose and steadfastness of will of the Pilgrim Fathers to those who shall come after us.
IRS990.Desc: Membership dues paid to the General Society of Mayflower Descendants in Plymouth MA. No grants were received or paid out. Dues received from Regular Members and Life Members.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: Payment of Application Fees to The General Society of Mayflower Descendants at Plymouth MA. Cost of lineage application processing by state Historians and certificates. Revenue of new prospective members paying application fees.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: Tri-annual Newsletter mailed to all members and prospective members

ProgSrvcAccomActyOtherGrp.Desc: Scholarship awarded to four Junior members.
Spring & Fall Membership Luncheons/meetings: meals, speaker fee, misc. venue expenses.
Stipends for three delegates to the General Society of Mayflower Descendants' annual General Board of Assistants meeting.
Dues billing, Directory, nametags, publicity, website, board meeting, etc.
General Liability and Commercial Crime Insuarance
Merchandise purchased for resale at Luncheons.
Donation to the Plimoth Plantation and to the Silver Books project of the General Society of Mayflower Descendants
